.TH MAKE.CONF 5 "2025-11-26" "Astral 5.3.1.6" "Astral Package Manager"
.SH NAME
make.conf \- Astral build configuration file
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fB/etc/astral/make.conf\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBmake.conf\fR is the main configuration file for the Astral package manager. It controls build flags, compiler options, and various features.

This file is sourced by \fBastral\fR at startup and affects all package builds.
.SH FILE FORMAT
The file uses simple shell variable assignments:

.nf
# Comments start with #
VARIABLE="value"
VARIABLE=$OTHER_VARIABLE
.fi

.SH VARIABLES
.SS Build Flags
.TP
\fBCFLAGS\fR
C compiler flags (default: \fB-O2 -pipe\fR)
.TP
\fBCXXFLAGS\fR
C++ compiler flags (default: same as CFLAGS)
.TP
\fBLDFLAGS\fR
Linker flags
.TP
\fBMAKEFLAGS\fR
Make flags (default: \fB-j$(nproc)\fR)

.SS Features
.TP
\fBFEATURES\fR
Space-separated list of features:
\fBccache\fR, \fBparallel-make\fR, \fBstrip\fR

.TP
\fBCCACHE_ENABLED\fR
Enable ccache support (\fByes\fR or \fBno\fR)

.SS Directories
.TP
\fBSTORE_DIR\fR
Content-addressed package store (default: \fB/astral/store\fR)
.TP
\fBRECIPES_DIR\fR
Local recipes directory (default: \fB/usr/src/astral/recipes\fR)
.TP
\fBCACHE_SRC\fR
Source cache directory (default: \fB/var/cache/astral/src\fR)
.TP
\fBDB_DIR\fR
Database directory (default: \fB/var/lib/astral/db\fR)

.SH EXAMPLE
.nf
# Build flags
CFLAGS="-O2 -pipe -march=native"
CXXFLAGS="$CFLAGS"
LDFLAGS=""
MAKEFLAGS="-j$(nproc)"

# Enable ccache
CCACHE_ENABLED="yes"

# Features
FEATURES="ccache parallel-make strip"
.fi

.SH FILES
.TP
\fB/etc/astral/make.conf\fR
Main configuration file
.TP
\fB/etc/astral/astral.stars\fR
Advanced configuration

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR astral (1),
.BR astral.stars (5)
